'''''Castles in the Air''''' (Italian:'''''Castelli in aria''''') is a 1939 Italian [[comedy film]] directed by [[Augusto Genina]] and starring [[Lilian Harvey]], [[Vittorio De Sica]] and [[Otto Treßler]].<ref>Moliterno p.80</ref> It was made at [[Cinecittà]] in [[Rome]], as part of a [[co-production (filmmaking)|co-production]] with Germany. A separate German-language version was also released. It is based on a novel by {{Interlanguage link multi|Franz Karl Franchy|de}}.

==Synopsis==
A [[wardrobe supervisor|wardrobe mistress]] at a [[Vienna]] theatre wins a competition, receiving as her prize a luxury tour round Italy. On the train she meets an impoverished young Italian who pretends to be a [[prince]].

==Partial cast==
* [[Lilian Harvey]] as Annie Wagner detta 'Mimì' 
* [[Vittorio De Sica]] as Riccardo Pietramola 
* [[Otto Treßler]] as Forster 
* [[Hilde von Stolz]] as La cantante 
* [[Fritz Odemar]] as Walter 
* [[Carla Sveva]] as La guardarobiera 
* [[Umberto Sacripante]] as Il gondoliere

